    "The GNN described above incorporates deep graph information up to L hops from the question entities.",
    "At each layer, it assigns importance to nodes based on their relations relevance to the question, as well as the probability of visiting their neighbor node in the previous layer.",
    "This approach parallels LLM-based KG traversal (Sun et al., 2024), where, starting from the question entities, the LLM iteratively selects relations and neighboring nodes to explore.",
    "Furthermore, to enable iterative KG traversal we reset the probability vector p (l) by",
    "Here, we impose the constraint that L must be even."
